 "size": 5188214, "title": "Image 4 of The patriot (Glenmora, La.), March 4, 1921, (Morning)", "width": 5320}, {"fulltext_service": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/lu/batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01/data/sn88064299/00295874867/1921030401/0275.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "mimetype": "text/plain", "use": "text"}], "pagination": {"current": 4, "first": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-04/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1", "from": 4, "last": null, "next": null, "of": 4, "page_list": [{"number": 1, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-04/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, {"number": 2, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-04/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=2"}, {"number": 3, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-04/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=3"}, {"number": 4, "url": null}], "perpage": 1, "perpage_options": [25, 50, 100, 150], "previous": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-04/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=3", "results": "4 - 4", "to": 4, "total": 4}, "previous_resource": {"label": "Previous Issue", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-02-25/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, "related_items": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2023655241/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/2fd46dd9-7ae5-5e47-83b5-411b0f59b769", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/collafc.afc2022010"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, aet", "xanamane, amonelath", "luangphone, nithy", "xanamane, phanat", "louangsouphom, chanthaly", "thongdy, kira", "ounechith, bouasone", "somchit, amy", "xanamane, samko", "haggood, sami", "xanamane, kingston", "malathong, vetsouvanh ning", "hamdani, badar", "xanamane, phouthone", "phoumylay, palixay", "nunez, heddy l.", "andrew w. mellon foundation", "phoumylay, khamsone", "khambounleuang, oubonlath alee", "sengsouly, khanthaly", "sengsouly, meng", "phoumylay, fancy", "american folklife center", "pakdi, inseng", "thalanh, sith"], "date": "2022", "dates": ["2022"], "description": ["The collection documents the many cultural facets and multi-generational perspectives of the Lao immigrant community and their New Year Festival at Wat Thammarattanaram, a Buddhist temple and monastery in Broussard (Iberia Parish), Louisiana. This temple serves as a religious and cultural center for Lao people in the area, hosting multiple cultural events throughout the year, with the largest one being the Louisiana Lao New Year (LLNY) celebrated annually on Easter weekend."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-16T06:37:16.329Z", "group": ["catalog-split-14", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-14"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["saint martin parish", "broussard", "louisiana", "glenmora", "iberia parish", "lafayette parish"], "number": ["2026-06-15t13:44:50.900000", "2023655241"], "original_format": ["manuscript/mixed material", "collection"], "partof": ["american folklife center", "catalog"], "score": 26.967804, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["social life and customs", "oral histories", "lao (tai people)", "interviews", "lao new year", "religious life and customs", "glenmora (la.)", "sound recordings", "louisiana", "video recordings", "iberia parish (la.)", "color", "digital photographs", "rites and ceremonies", "broussard (lafayette parish and saint martin parish, la.)", "buddhism and culture", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2026-06-16T07:09:11.517Z", "title": "Lao Buddhist New Year Festival in Southern Louisiana : Community Collections Grant Project, 2022", "type": ["manuscript"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/2023655241"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_002_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_002_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, phouthone", "hamdani, badar", "xanamane, phanat"], "date": "2022-10-06", "dates": ["2022-10-06"], "description": ["Phouthone Xanamane discusses the history of Laos Americans and the tribulations it took to not only leave Laos but to start a whole new life in America. Interview is conducted in Laotian."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_002_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_002/afc2022010_002_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_002/afc2022010_002_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 5, "language": ["english", "lao"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["community collections grant project", "american folklife center", "lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_002_mv001", "subject": ["ethnography", "social life and customs", "lao (tai people)", "interviews", "moving image", "louisiana", "rites and ceremonies", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Phouthone Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_002_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_009_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_009_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, aet", "hamdani, badar", "xanamane, phanat"], "date": "2022-03-31", "dates": ["2022-03-31"], "description": ["Aet Xanamane is a former pageant queen and speaks of her experience as a member of the Nang San Khan. She also talks about immigrating and growing up in the community. She gives an engrossing first-person account of how the American Laos Villages came to be and the work the community undertook to build their temple. This interview is conducted mostly in Lao."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_009_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_009/afc2022010_009_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_009/afc2022010_009_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 6, "language": ["english", "lao"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["community collections grant project", "american folklife center", "lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_009_mv001", "subject": ["ethnography", "social life and customs", "lao (tai people)", "interviews", "lao new year", "moving image", "louisiana", "nang san khan", "rites and ceremonies", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Aet Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_009_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_012_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_012_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, amonelath", "hamdani, badar", "xanamane, phanat"], "date": "2022-03-31", "dates": ["2022-03-31"], "description": ["Amonleth Xanamane demonstrates how to cook a typical Laotian dish and her family's favorite: Kao piek. While cooking she talks about passing on her traditions to her younger girls and how much of a struggle it can be to keep alive a culture when you experience it second hand."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_012_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_012/afc2022010_012_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_012/afc2022010_012_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["community collections grant project", "american folklife center", "lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_012_mv001", "subject": ["ethnography", "social life and customs", "lao (tai people)", "interviews", "moving image", "louisiana", "cooking, lao", "rites and ceremonies", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Amonelath Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_012_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_013_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_013_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, kingston", "hamdani, badar", "xanamane, samko", "xanamane, phanat"], "date": "2022-03-31", "dates": ["2022-03-31"], "description": ["Samko Xanamane talks briefly about his own experiences of being sent to America as a teenager without knowing any English; especially coming to rural central Louisiana where he was the first encounter many Americans had had with Asian immigrants. He also explains the festival parade, why the floats are so extravagant and how the judging works."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_013_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_013/afc2022010_013_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_013/afc2022010_013_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["community collections grant project", "american folklife center", "lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_013_mv001", "subject": ["ethnography", "social life and customs", "lao (tai people)", "interviews", "lao new year", "moving image", "louisiana", "rites and ceremonies", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Samko Xanamane and Kingston Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_013_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/collections/lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana/about-this-collection/", "https://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "https://www.loc.gov/item/2023655241", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2023655241/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/collafc.afc2022010"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, aet", "xanamane, amonelath", "luangphone, nithy", "xanamane, phanat", "louangsouphom, chanthaly", "thongdy, kira", "ounechith, bouasone", "somchit, amy", "xanamane, samko", "haggood, sami", "xanamane, kingston", "malathong, vetsouvanh ning", "hamdani, badar", "xanamane, phouthone", "phoumylay, palixay", "nunez, heddy l.", "andrew w. mellon foundation", "phoumylay, khamsone", "khambounleuang, oubonlath alee", "sengsouly, khanthaly", "sengsouly, meng", "phoumylay, fancy", "american folklife center", "pakdi, inseng", "thalanh, sith"], "count": 32, "date": "2022", "dates": ["2022"], "description": ["This collection documents the 2022 Louisiana Lao New Year Festival (LLNY) presented April 15-17, 2022, by Wat Thammarattanaram, a Buddhist temple and monastery in Broussard (Iberia Parish), Louisiana. With the support of a 2022 Community Collections Grant (CCG) from the American Folklife Center's Of the People: Widening the Path! initiative, a community-based research team led by project director Phanat Xanamane, videographer Bader Hamdani, historian Dr. Shane Bernard, and assistant director Sami Sion Haggood documented the social, cultural and environmental expressions that have shaped this important cultural celebration over its 30+ year history."], 